{
  "texts": [
    "The user can iteratively repeat the clustering process until they are satisfied that all pertinent papers have been incorporated into the analysis.",
    "Iris.ai also enables users to further filter the papers according to a variety of facets.",
    "Minimum requirements: Generally, the accuracy of a classifier improves with an increasing number of annotated papers, but this also increases the time and effort required from researchers.",
    "Most methods need between 1-15 relevant papers and typically the same number of irrelevant ones.",
    "This is a relatively low number that should allow researchers to quickly annotate the initial set of seed papers."
  ]
}